Solution 0 suggests wearing the wedding ring on the ring finger of the right hand, while Solution 1 recommends wearing it on the ring finger of the left hand.

The ring finger, by definition, is the finger on the fourth finger of the hand, which is typically the fourth finger of the left hand for most people. This is because the ancient Romans and Egyptians believed that this finger contained the "vena amoris," or vein that led directly to the heart.

In modern times, this tradition has been adopted by many cultures, and it is generally accepted that the left ring finger is the correct place to wear a wedding ring. This is because the left hand is often associated with the heart, and wearing the ring on this finger is a symbolic representation of the bond between two people.

Therefore, based on this reasoning, Solution 1 is the correct answer.

