final_output_text: To easily prep garlic, we need to remove the outer layers of skin and break the garlic into individual cloves. This can be achieved through two methods, both of which involve shaking the garlic to loosen the skins. 

First, we remove the outer layers of skin and break the garlic into individual cloves. This is a crucial step as it allows us to access the edible part of the garlic, which is the inner clove. 

Next, we place the cloves in a large container, such as a garbage bag or a Tupepeware container. The choice of container is not crucial, as long as it is large enough to hold the garlic cloves. 

Now, we shake the container as hard as you can for about a minute or two. This action helps to loosen the skins from the cloves, making it easier to remove them. The force of the shaking action helps to dislodge the skins, allowing us to easily remove them. 

After shaking, we check the garlic to see if most of the skins have come off. If not, we give the container another quick shake to loosen the remaining skins. Some cloves may still require manual peeling, but this method has significantly reduced the time and effort required. 

