final_output_text: To make a PB&J, we need to follow a specific sequence of steps. Here's a step-by-Step-by-Step explanation:

1. Start by taking two slices of bread. This is the foundation of our PB&J, so make sure you have two slices ready.

2. Next, take the peanut butter and spread it on one side of one slice of bread. This is the main component of our sandwich. You can use as much or as little peanut butter as you like, but make sure to cover the entire side of the bread.

3. Now, take the jelly and spread it on the other side of the other slice of bread. This is the sweet and fruity counterpart to the savory peanut butter.

4. Once you've spread the jelly on the second slice of bread, it's time to bring the two slices together. Place the slice with the jelly facing the slice with the peanut butter.

5. Press down gently on the two slices to ensure they stick together. This will create a delicious and satisfying sandwich.

