final_output_text: To use a zipper, follow these steps:

1. Locate the zipper, which is typically a long strip of fabric or plastic with interlocking teeth on either side.
2. Identify the direction of the zipper, which is usually indicated by arrows or a label. The arrows usually show the direction of the zipper's movement, with the top arrow pointing towards the top of the zipper and the bottom arrow pointing towards the bottom.
3. Hold the zipper in one hand, with the teeth facing upwards or downwards, depending on the direction of the zipper.
4. If you want to close the zipper, grasp the zipper tab or pull the zipper pull, which is usually located at the top of the zipper. This will start to move the teeth together, closing the zipper.
5. If you want to open the zipper, grasp the zipper tab or pull the zipper pull in the opposite direction, which is usually towards the bottom of the zipper. This will start to move the teeth apart, opening the zipper.
6. Continue pulling or pushing the zipper in the desired direction until the zipper is fully closed or open.

